```gitignore
# Byte-compiled / optimized / DLL files
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyd
*.pyo
*.exe
*.dll
*.so

# IDE-specific files
.vscode/
.idea/

# Jupyter Notebook / IPython files
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# Python environment
virtualenv/
venv/
env/
.env

# Data files
# Consider using Git LFS for large data files instead of ignoring them
# *.csv
# *.xlsx
# *.hdf5

# Colab-specific files
# Files generated by Google Colab, often temporary or sensitive
/content/drive/
/content/sample_data/
*.ipynb_metadata

# Checkpoints or saved models
# If you save models frequently and they are large, consider Git LFS or ignoring
# and storing them separately.
*.pt
*.pth
*.h5

# Log files
*.log

# Temporary files
*~
*.bak
*.swp

# User-specific configuration (often contains secrets)
# For example, API keys or sensitive configurations. Use environment variables or Colab secrets instead.
# config.ini
# .env

# Any other files you want to ignore
# For example, if you download a large dataset temporarily:
# large_dataset_folder/
```
